{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-8c1998b37d1e092a", "type": "tool_result", "content": "# InstructAudio: Unified speech and music generation with natural language instruction\narXiv: 2511.18487\nAuthors: Chunyu Qiang, Kang Yin, Xiaopeng Wang, Yuzhe Liang, Jiahui Zhao, Ruibo Fu, Tianrui Wang, Cheng Gong, Chen Zhang, Longbiao Wang, Jianwu Dang\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We introduce a joint modeling framework for speech and music generation based on a multimodal diffusion transformer architecture.\n  2. We achieve unified text-based control over speech and music generation through a standardized instruction-phoneme input format encompassing timbre, paralinguistic, and musical attributes while supporting dialogue generation.\n  3. Experimental results demonstrate state-of-the-art performance in instruction-based text-to-speech while maintaining competitive text-to-music capabilities.\n\nTags: TTS, TTS/架构-NAR-Flow, TTS/控制-NL描述, TTS/控制-指令合成, 压缩, 压缩/量化-VAE\n===\n# UniMoE-Audio: Unified Speech and Music Generation with Dynamic-Capacity MoE\narXiv: 2510.13344\nAuthors: Zhenyu Liu, Yunxin Li, Xuanyu Zhang, Qixun Teng, Shenyuan Jiang, Xinyu Chen, Haoyuan Shi, Jinchao Li, Qi Wang, Haolan Chen, Fanbo Meng, Mingjun Zhao, Yu Xu, Yancheng He, Baotian Hu, Min Zhang\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We propose UniMoE-Audio, a unified speech and music generation model based on a novel Dynamic-Capacity MoE framework that integrates a Top-P routing strategy and a hybrid expert design to mitigate inherent task conflict.\n  2. We introduce a data-aware, three-stage training curriculum that systematically overcomes data imbalance through independent specialist training, router warmup, and synergistic joint training.\n  3. We provide extensive experiments demonstrating that UniMoE-Audio achieves state-of-the-art or competitive performance on major speech and music generation benchmarks while revealing valuable insights into the dynamic activation patterns of the unified MoE model.\n\nTags: TTS\n===\n# DashengTokenizer: One layer is enough for unified audio understanding and generation\narXiv: 2602.23765\nAuthors: Heinrich Dinkel, Xingwei Sun, Gang Li, Jiahao Mei, Yadong Niu, Jizhong Liu, Xiyang Li, Yifan Liao, Jiahao Zhou, Junbo Zhang, Jian Luan\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: codec_vae\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. DashengTokenizer introduces a unified continuous audio tokenizer that embeds low-dimensional acoustic information into high-dimensional frozen semantic features via a simple linear projection.\n  2. The proposed acoustic injection method significantly outperforms previous audio codecs and encoders in linear evaluation across 22 diverse audio understanding tasks while maintaining competitive reconstruction quality.\n  3. A semantic preservation loss is introduced to prevent acoustic features from overwhelming semantic representations, effectively bridging the gap between understanding and generation.\n  4. The tokenizer achieves superior performance in speech enhancement, yielding higher objective quality and speaker similarity compared to existing encoder baselines.\n  5. DashengTokenizer surpasses standard VAE-based methods on text-to-audio and text-to-music generation tasks while also demonstrating significantly faster training convergence.\n  6. The results challenge the prevailing assumption that VAE-based architectures are a prerequisite for audio synthesis.\n\nTags: 压缩, 压缩/语义声学-语义, 压缩/语义声学-声学, 压缩/语义声学-混合", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "dbcb9227-d72e-45fa-85a9-e4fdc9bb82ea", "uuid": "4a7f4723-14b7-4b21-90a4-ada974668d62", "timestamp": "2026-07-23T09:10:26.596Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "# InstructAudio: Unified speech and music generation with natural language instruction\narXiv: 2511.18487\nAuthors: Chunyu Qiang, Kang Yin, Xiaopeng Wang, Yuzhe Liang, Jiahui Zhao, Ruibo Fu, Tianrui Wang, Cheng Gong, Chen Zhang, Longbiao Wang, Jianwu Dang\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We introduce a joint modeling framework for speech and music generation based on a multimodal diffusion transformer architecture.\n  2. We achieve unified text-based control over speech and music generation through a standardized instruction-phoneme input format encompassing timbre, paralinguistic, and musical attributes while supporting dialogue generation.\n  3. Experimental results demonstrate state-of-the-art performance in instruction-based text-to-speech while maintaining competitive text-to-music capabilities.\n\nTags: TTS, TTS/架构-NAR-Flow, TTS/控制-NL描述, TTS/控制-指令合成, 压缩, 压缩/量化-VAE\n===\n# UniMoE-Audio: Unified Speech and Music Generation with Dynamic-Capacity MoE\narXiv: 2510.13344\nAuthors: Zhenyu Liu, Yunxin Li, Xuanyu Zhang, Qixun Teng, Shenyuan Jiang, Xinyu Chen, Haoyuan Shi, Jinchao Li, Qi Wang, Haolan Chen, Fanbo Meng, Mingjun Zhao, Yu Xu, Yancheng He, Baotian Hu, Min Zhang\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We propose UniMoE-Audio, a unified speech and music generation model based on a novel Dynamic-Capacity MoE framework that integrates a Top-P routing strategy and a hybrid expert design to mitigate inherent task conflict.\n  2. We introduce a data-aware, three-stage training curriculum that systematically overcomes data imbalance through independent specialist training, router warmup, and synergistic joint training.\n  3. We provide extensive experiments demonstrating that UniMoE-Audio achieves state-of-the-art or competitive performance on major speech and music generation benchmarks while revealing valuable insights into the dynamic activation patterns of the unified MoE model.\n\nTags: TTS\n===\n# DashengTokenizer: One layer is enough for unified audio understanding and generation\narXiv: 2602.23765\nAuthors: Heinrich Dinkel, Xingwei Sun, Gang Li, Jiahao Mei, Yadong Niu, Jizhong Liu, Xiyang Li, Yifan Liao, Jiahao Zhou, Junbo Zhang, Jian Luan\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: codec_vae\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. DashengTokenizer introduces a unified continuous audio tokenizer that embeds low-dimensional acoustic information into high-dimensional frozen semantic features via a simple linear projection.\n  2. The proposed acoustic injection method significantly outperforms previous audio codecs and encoders in linear evaluation across 22 diverse audio understanding tasks while maintaining competitive reconstruction quality.\n  3. A semantic preservation loss is introduced to prevent acoustic features from overwhelming semantic representations, effectively bridging the gap between understanding and generation.\n  4. The tokenizer achieves superior performance in speech enhancement, yielding higher objective quality and speaker similarity compared to existing encoder baselines.\n  5. DashengTokenizer surpasses standard VAE-based methods on text-to-audio and text-to-music generation tasks while also demonstrating significantly faster training convergence.\n  6. The results challenge the prevailing assumption that VAE-based architectures are a prerequisite for audio synthesis.\n\nTags: 压缩, 压缩/语义声学-语义, 压缩/语义声学-声学, 压缩/语义声学-混合", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
